INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('829', '1', '2014-02-28 06:15:22', '2014-02-28 06:15:22', '<h2 id=\"areaFocus\">Prince George\'s County H1-B and Temporary Visa Attorneys</h2>\r\nYour status as a documented immigrant in the United States is not permanent. Modifications based on changes in circumstances occur often, requiring the type of service that we provide at Odelugo &amp; Johnson, LLC, in Hyattsville, Maryland.<img class=\"alignright  wp-image-830\" alt=\"i-prac-permresadjofstatus\" src=\"http://odelugojohnsonllc.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/i-prac-permresadjofstatus.jpg\" width=\"193\" height=\"253\" />\r\n\r\nTime is of the essence in applying for permanent residency or an adjustment of status. Depending on the situation, the process can be immediate or it can take a certain amount of time.\r\n<h3>Bringing Married Couples and Families Together</h3>\r\nThe prospect of uniting couples and reuniting families is a rewarding yet complicated part of our immigration practice at Odelugo &amp; Johnson, LLC. Many immigrants who come to the United States for purposes of work find a spouse here.\r\n\r\nMarriage to a U.S. citizen will result in an immediate permanent resident card. Even marriage to a permanent resident will allow you to enjoy the same status, just not as quickly. Urgency also exists when you are seeking to have your spouse, parents and children under 21 join you in this country.\r\n<h3>Simple or Complex Processes Involved</h3>\r\nWe communicate our knowledge of the law and processes related to it to our clients. Different status requires different lengths of processing times in securing a permanent resident card. We help clients throughout the entire process of changing their status or receiving a permanent resident card.\r\n\r\nThe first step is immediately filing an application. Whether your application will move through the process quickly or slowly, the timing of the application is important. Many times, residents of a certain country are forced to wait.\r\n\r\nOur office is within walking distance from the metro. You may take the Green Line to Prince Georges Plaza. We are near Prince Georges Plaza Mall in the new development of University Town Center. We are accessible from the Beltway and Interstates 495 and 95 near Montgomery County and Washington, D.C. and free parking is available.\r\n<h3>Contact Us</h3>\r\nTo get more information or to schedule an appointment with an experienced lawyer, please contact us.', 'Permanent Residency Adjustment Of Status', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'permanent-residency-adjustment-of-status', '', '', '2014-03-05 06:44:46', '2014-03-05 06:44:46', '', '0', 'http://odelugojohnsonllc.com/?page_id=829', '0', 'page', '', '0');
