INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('910', '1', '2013-02-07 07:50:15', '2013-02-07 07:50:15', '<div>\r\n\r\nAs a whole, sports are considered to be good for children and adults alike. They combat obesity, are healthy for the heart and lungs, and keep people in shape. However, there are certain sports that health professionals consider too dangerous to continue, at least for children. Most of these sports involve a greater risk of serious head or spinal injuries as well as broken bones.\r\n\r\nA children\'s sport that has been gaining popularity over the past few years is youth mixed martial arts, also known as Pankration. This mixed martial arts sport has been called violent and dangerous by opponents. Maryland is among several states that have introduced legislation to address the concerns related to the safety of this sport.\r\n\r\nAlthough rules set forth by the United States Fight League prohibit children under age 16 from hitting opponents in the head, serious injuries can still occur, say leading pediatricians. The director of the National Center for Catastrophic Sport Injury Research says severe trauma can result from the violent actions of this sport. Damage to the neck and spine, including paralysis, are risks. He believes youth MMA should be banned.\r\n\r\nA pediatric sports medicine specialist and member of the American Academy of Pediatrics Council on Sports Medicine and Fitness calls youth MMA troubling due to the potential for permanent disability by concussions and other injuries.\r\n\r\nFor now, it\'s up to parents to decide whether to allow their children to participate in this sport or to put them into something less combative. From a personal injury perspective, the possibility exists for local or national leagues -- or even parents themselves -- being held liable for injuries sustained during the participation of dangerous sports.\r\n\r\n<strong>Source</strong>: HLNTV.com, \"<a href=\"http://www.hlntv.com/article/2013/02/02/young-mma-fighters\" target=\"_blank\">Kids punch, kick &amp; tackle their way to the top</a>,\" Allison Gilbert, Feb. 2, 2013\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Concussions, spinal cord injuries among dangers of youth MMA', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'concussions-spinal-cord-injuries-among-dangers-of-youth-mma', '', '', '2014-02-28 07:51:14', '2014-02-28 07:51:14', '', '0', 'http://odelugojohnsonllc.com/?p=910', '0', 'post', '', '0');
