INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('926', '1', '2013-12-19 09:38:26', '2013-12-19 09:38:26', '<div>\r\n\r\nThese days, most people may agree that something like a minor cold can be a major setback when it comes to working and taking care of a family. And even when an individual has medical insurance in Maryland, they still may not be able to afford to experience any kind of ailment and/or medical complication. One womans life will forever be impacted by a seemingly straightforward medical procedure she underwent years ago. Now, shes attempting to hold her doctors responsible for allegedly causing her permanent disability in a major medical malpractice lawsuit.\r\n\r\nThe plaintiff in the medical malpractice lawsuit underwent laparoscopic surgery to remove an ectopic pregnancy in October of 2009. The woman and mother of a teenage daughter claims that she was discharged from the hospital only days after the procedure even though she was still in extreme pain. She was ultimately readmitted to the hospital for emergency surgery and care.\r\n\r\nAfter waking up in the hospital weeks later, the woman claims that she learned she had suffered from sepsis and gangrene, which resulted in both her legs being amputated from the knee down. The plaintiff also sustained scarring to other parts of her body and now suffers from hearing loss caused by the aggressive antibiotic treatment required to treat her infection.\r\n\r\nDuring the course of the malpractice trial an expert testified that the medical complications leading to the womans medical crisis could have been avoided. Surgeons allegedly punctured the womans colon during her initial surgery.\r\n\r\nThe hospital argues that doctors responded appropriately to the womans medical condition and saved her life. However, she contends that her mobility and way of life have been seriously affected by her double amputation.\r\n\r\n<b>Source:</b>New York Daily News, <a href=\"http://www.nydailynews.com/new-york/brooklyn/eclusive-hospital-victim-procedure-worse-article-1.1537002\" target=\"_blank\">EXCLUSIVE: Hospital victim says procedure led to legs being amputated: It was a sharp, driving pain. And it kept getting wors</a>e, Oren Yaniv, Dec. 4, 201\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Double amputation may have been caused by surgical error', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'double-amputation-may-have-been-caused-by-surgical-error', '', '', '2014-02-28 09:39:51', '2014-02-28 09:39:51', '', '0', 'http://odelugojohnsonllc.com/?p=926', '0', 'post', '', '0');
