INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('932', '1', '2013-11-15 09:46:48', '2013-11-15 09:46:48', '<div>\r\n\r\nAt some point in many peoples lives, they and their families consider the option of placing a loved one in a care facility. After all, thousands of elderly people in Maryland and other states around the country require some level of daily assistance and care. Assisted living facilities are known for providing patients with various degrees of services, but there are mounting concerns over the fact that injury and medical malpractice incidents may be on the rise and largely condoned by the assisted living industry due to a lack of federal oversight.\r\n\r\nWhereas nursing home facilities are largely subject to federal regulation, assisted living facilities typically function independently and are monitored by state agencies. Because assisted living homes do not receive federal funding, some industry insiders claim that they are better able to serve their communities. A recent investigatory piece by ProPublica and Frontline raises concerns, however, over how a lack of federal regulation may be contributing to negligence and poor care standards at assisted living facilities everywhere.\r\n\r\nAccording to the article, many residents of assisted living facilities require a level attention and medical care not offered. A lack of staffing qualifications and requirements, along with patient overcrowding, could be leading to compromised patient care and safety at many facilities around the nation. And researchers claim that the situation may be compounded by the fact that assisted living homes are not inspected as often as federally-regulated nursing homes.\r\n\r\nAnd while some argue that imposing federal guidelines on the assisted living industry could go a long way to improve patient care and streamline regulatory procedures, the situation remains that issues like state budget cuts and poorly enforced legislation are likely contributing to questionable industry practices.\r\n\r\n<b>Source:</b>propublica.org, <a href=\"http://www.propublica.org/article/elderly-at-risk-and-haphazardly-protected\" target=\"_blank\">Elderly, At Risk, and Haphazardly Protected</a>, A.C. Thompson, Jonathan Jones, Oct. 29, 2013\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Assisted living facility negligence may largely go overlooked', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'assisted-living-facility-negligence-may-largely-go-overlooked', '', '', '2014-02-28 09:47:58', '2014-02-28 09:47:58', '', '0', 'http://odelugojohnsonllc.com/?p=932', '0', 'post', '', '0');
