INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('934', '1', '2013-10-31 09:48:14', '2013-10-31 09:48:14', '<div>\r\n\r\nAs baseball fans throughout Maryland and the entire country root for their favorite teams and players, they can be unaware of any disputes that take place off the field. For instance, many fans may not know when or how severely some players are injured in the game, or what other employment-related issues players can face. Not only is one MLB player in the midst of a major dispute with his team and league over a possible suspension but he is also pursuing a medical malpractice lawsuit against his attending physician and hospital.\r\n\r\nAlex Rodriguez did not play much of this year because of left hip surgery he underwent in January. He returned to the game in August, and the Yankees team contends that A-Rod didnt complain about his left hip prior to surgery. He had already undergone surgery for his right hip four years ago. However, A-Rod argues that he was forced to play baseball even though his left hip was seriously injured at the time.\r\n\r\nIn his recently filed medical malpractice lawsuit, A-Rod claims that the physician that treated him concealed the nature of his hip injury, allowing him to play when he shouldnt have. A hospital in New York is also identified as a defendant in the case. A-Rod argues that he suffered emotional distress and anguish as a result of the mistreatment he allegedly endured, along with pain and suffering. Although, there is no information on what damages, if any, he is seeking in the case.\r\n\r\nThe question may be raised whether the plaintiffs claims should be addressed to his players union or the Major League Baseball association. These accusations come as the baseball player confronts disputes with the baseball commissioner, the MLB, and the MLB Players Association over an impending game suspension.\r\n\r\n<b>Source:</b>thespec.com, <a href=\"http://www.thespec.com/sports-story/4145402-mlb-a-rod-suing-yankees-team-doctor-new-york-city-hospital-over-pain-agony-distress-/\" target=\"_blank\">MLB: A-Rod suing Yankees team doctor, New York City hospital over \'pain, agony, distress\'</a>, David B. Caruso, Oct. 7, 2013\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Major baseball player files medical malpractice suit', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'major-baseball-player-files-medical-malpractice-suit', '', '', '2014-02-28 09:49:05', '2014-02-28 09:49:05', '', '0', 'http://odelugojohnsonllc.com/?p=934', '0', 'post', '', '0');
