INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('936', '1', '2013-10-25 09:49:20', '2013-10-25 09:49:20', '<div>\r\n\r\nWhile the majority of babies born in Maryland and other states around the country are happy and healthy, thousands of others come into the world with serious medical conditions and/or injuries. The birthing process can be incredibly stressful on babies, and sometimes complications result in newborns sustaining injuries. In many instances, then, the question is whether or not such injuries could have been avoided and whether they were caused by factors like negligence or medical errors. A recent medical malpractice lawsuit over a child who allegedly sustained permanent birth injuries illustrates how complex these types of cases can be.\r\n\r\nThe child in the case has no use of her right arm due to severe nerve damage she sustained during delivery in an Alabama hospital. According to the childs mother and legal representation, a series of nerves running up her hand, through her shoulder and into her spinal column were permanently injured by her obstetrician in the process of attempting to guide her through the birth canal. The plaintiffs in the case argue that the doctor caused the permanent damage by handling the babys body too forcefully, and that she failed to recommend delivery by C-section in the first place.\r\n\r\nThe presiding judge and jury also heard from the defense, who argued that the obstetrician handle the entire delivery appropriately. They contend that a C-section was ultimately required because of complications involving the babys size. The defendant testified during the course of the two-week trial, along with experts on both sides of the case.\r\n\r\nUltimately, the jury decided that the injuries sustained by the baby were not caused by the defendant.\r\n\r\n<b>Source:</b>al.com, <a href=\"http://blog.al.com/breaking/2013/10/after_long_trial_jury_finds_ma.html\" target=\"_blank\">After long trial jury finds Madison obstetrician did not commit malpractice</a>, Brian Lawson, Oct. 4, 2013\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Physician found not liable in birth injury case', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'physician-found-not-liable-in-birth-injury-case', '', '', '2014-02-28 09:50:18', '2014-02-28 09:50:18', '', '0', 'http://odelugojohnsonllc.com/?p=936', '0', 'post', '', '0');
