INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('956', '1', '2013-08-05 10:04:32', '2013-08-05 10:04:32', '<div>\r\n\r\nThe death of a loved one due to cancer and other serious diseases is devastating. When the disease may have been prevented, it is even more heartbreaking. Fortunately, researchers are working find the reasons behind medical malpractice cases, which may improve the quality of care that Maryland patients receive.\r\n\r\nEven as doctors learn more about deadly diseases such as cancer and heart disease, they still fail to recognize warning signs for these types of diseases. One recent study indicates that a substantial number of medical malpractice cases are due to missed diagnoses. When doctors fail to recognize the signs for illnesses such as cancer and heart disease, patients may become progressively worse. In some cases, patients suffer an early death as a result of the doctors error.\r\n\r\nBecause health care providers can face costly lawsuits for failing to diagnose a patient, some doctors have been encouraged to order more tests and treatments just to make sure that theyre not missing any critical diagnoses. Unfortunately, this practice also drives up the cost of health care. Although doctors are ultimately responsible for detecting and treating potentially life-threatening illness, it may be a good idea for patients to closely monitor their own health.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately, in the United States only about one-third of victims of missed diagnoses receive compensation. By comparison, about 50 percent of victims in the United Kingdom receive settlements. It is possible that some people fail to connect a doctors missed diagnosis to an untimely death, and the doctor is never held responsible for his or her error. It may be helpful for people in this situation to work with an attorney.\r\n\r\n<b>Source:</b>CBS News, <a href=\"http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-204_162-57594570/most-common-medical-malpractice-claims-for-missed-cancer-heart-attacks/\" target=\"_blank\">Most common medical malpractice claims for missed cancer, heart attacks</a>, Ryan Jaslow, July 19, 2013\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Study points out prevalence of missed diagnoses', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'study-points-out-prevalence-of-missed-diagnoses', '', '', '2014-02-28 10:05:37', '2014-02-28 10:05:37', '', '0', 'http://odelugojohnsonllc.com/?p=956', '0', 'post', '', '0');
