INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('962', '1', '2013-07-02 10:14:30', '2013-07-02 10:14:30', '<div>\r\n\r\nGoing into surgery is a scary event for most people, since they lose control of their consciousness as well as what happens to them while theyre under the knife. Mistakes with anesthesia are a valid concern, especially since it can be so easy to make a mistake with the medication administered during surgery. Surgical errors involving anesthesia are one of the causes of medical malpractice cases in Maryland as well as the rest of the country.\r\n\r\nA brother and sister have filed a lawsuit against Wake Forest University Health Sciences and North Carolina Baptist Hospital, claiming the centers were responsible for their fathers death. The 60-year-old man had gone to the emergency room suffering from kidney issues and diarrhea. After being admitted to the ICU with severe issues including bacterial pneumonia and hypotension, his condition started to improve. He underwent surgery for gastric perforation soon after.\r\n\r\nThe anesthesiologist made a mistake with his medication, giving him Sufentanil, a drug 10 times more potent than the Fentanyl he should have received. In addition, Sufentanil is risky in patients with kidney dysfunction, and the dosage should be carefully monitored with consideration to body weight, physical status, and other crucial factors.\r\n\r\nWhen the anesthesiologist realized her error, she notified the surgical team, but the drug Narcan to counter the Sufentanils effects was never administered. Eight days after his surgery, the man died of organ and respiratory failure.\r\n\r\nThe mans son and daughter are seeking over $10,000 in damages for the loss of their father. Its extremely difficult to lose a parent, and even more tragic when the death is a result of medical professional negligence. Some medical malpractice cases can spur hospitals into taking better precautions to prevent these tragedies from happening.\r\n\r\n<b>Source:</b>The Dispatch, <a href=\"http://www.the-dispatch.com/article/20130620/NEWS/306209985/1005?p=1&amp;tc=pg\" target=\"_blank\">Siblings file medical malpractice suit over death of father</a>, Darrick Ignasiak, June 20, 2013\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Anesthesia error causes father\'s death', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'anesthesia-error-causes-fathers-death', '', '', '2014-02-28 10:16:29', '2014-02-28 10:16:29', '', '0', 'http://odelugojohnsonllc.com/?p=962', '0', 'post', '', '0');
