INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('964', '1', '2013-06-12 10:17:10', '2013-06-12 10:17:10', '<div>\r\n\r\nIf you are injured as a result of a doctor error, its important to file a claim within the required time period. Laws exist in Maryland and other states that require patients to file medical malpractice claims within a certain time frame, or the case could be tossed out.\r\n\r\nThe Wyoming Supreme Court reversed a previous ruling from the states district court that initially disqualified a mans medical malpractice lawsuit against Cheyenne Regional Medical Center. Originally, the district court ruled that the man failed to file his lawsuit within the two-year required time period.\r\n\r\nWhen the man was hospitalized for pneumonia complications in 2007, a hospital employee injured his shoulder and arm while attempting to move him in bed. He received physical and occupational therapy for his injury, and continued to seek treatment after being released from the hospital when he couldnt move his shoulder. A neurologist diagnosed him with a brachial plexus injury, which damaged the nerves running from his shoulder to his arm and hand.\r\n\r\nThe man filed a negligence lawsuit against the hospital in 2010. The hospital requested the court to dismiss the claim, saying he had missed the two-year deadline. However, Supreme Court justices ruled that the continuous treatment the man had received during and after his hospital stay meant he had filed just within the deadline parameters.\r\n\r\nAttorneys say the issue of misinterpreting deadlines and the continuous treatment rule is common. This is an important reason to be sure an experienced personal injury attorney is representing you, in case any of the laws regarding medical professional negligence and hospital mistakes are interpreted wrong by the court.\r\n\r\n<b>Source:</b>Wyoming Tribune Eagle, <a href=\"http://www.wyomingnews.com/articles/2013/05/30/news/19local_05-30-13.txt\" target=\"_blank\">Wyoming Supreme Court reverses malpractice ruling</a>, Kelsey Bray, May 30, 2013\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Supreme Court reverses medical malpractice ruling over time issue', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'supreme-court-reverses-medical-malpractice-ruling-over-time-issue', '', '', '2014-02-28 10:18:22', '2014-02-28 10:18:22', '', '0', 'http://odelugojohnsonllc.com/?p=964', '0', 'post', '', '0');
