INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('984', '1', '2012-12-26 10:39:00', '2012-12-26 10:39:00', 'In our Hyattsville office, we assist clients who have been the victim of medical malpractice, spinal cord injuries, birth injuries and other devastating harm. Because of the nature of our practice, we stay abreast of developments with regard to these areas. At least once a week, we will write a post on one of them and publish it here.\r\n\r\nRecently, we came across news coverage of a study that was published in the medical journal Surgery. This study found that \"never events\" -- instances of medical malpractice that are so bad they should never happen -- actually occur about 500 times a year in the U.S.\r\n\r\n\"Never events\" include things such as operating on the wrong body part or performing the wrong type of surgery. Almost half the instances examined by researchers involved a doctor or nurse leaving a foreign object, like a surgical sponge, inside a patient after an operation.\r\n\r\nIn the data that researchers used for incidents between 2004 and 2010, 59 percent of those who were the victim of a \"never event\" suffered a temporary injury, 33 percent suffered a permanent injury and, most tragically of all, 7 percent died.\r\n\r\nWe do not bring you this news to alarm you. Rather, we think it is important to be an informed consumer of healthcare and to know that, if anything bad happens to you when you are seeking medical treatment, you have rights and options.\r\n\r\n<strong>Source: </strong>RedOrbit, \"<a href=\"http://www.redorbit.com/news/health/1112752755/medical-errors-commonplace-surgery-122112/\" target=\"_blank\">Study Shows Medical Errors Are Common In Surgery</a>,\" Dec. 21, 2012', 'Medical malpractice study: 500 \'never events\' occur each year', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'medical-malpractice-study-500-never-events-occur-each-year', '', '', '2014-02-28 10:41:02', '2014-02-28 10:41:02', '', '0', 'http://odelugojohnsonllc.com/?p=984', '0', 'post', '', '0');
